Cook the potatoes with the garlic cloves in a large pan of salted boiling water for 15–20 minutes, or until tender.Drain the potatoes and push through a potato ricer. Heat the cream in another large pan, then add the potato and the olive oil and season with lemon juice and white wine vinegar.To make the lamb chops, heat the oil in a frying pan. Season the chops and cook for 3–4 minutes on each side for pink, juicy lamb; cook longer for well done.Mix together the dressing ingredients in a bowl and season with salt and pepper.To serve, spoon the skordalia potatoes onto serving plates, top with a lamb chop and spoon over the dressing.